div1.p: IN THE CIRCUIT COURT OF THE UNITED STATES ON THE NINTH CIRCUIT, DISTRICT OF WASHINGTON, NORTHERN DIVISION.
In the Matter of the Petition of H. C. LITTOOY for a Writ of Habeas Corpus. 1207

Comes now Edward Cudihee and moves to dismiss the writ of Habeas Corpus herein and also the petition upon which the same has been issued, upon the ground and for the reason that the petition herein is wholly insufficient to confer jurisdiction upon this Court, and because the facts and allegations therein are not germane and should not be included in said petition.
He especially moves to strike from the petition paragraph 2 of said petition, and paragraphs 6, 7, 8, 9 and 10 of said petition because the same are wholly irrelevant to be included therein.

This defendant, further answering, moves to dismiss said petition upon the ground that the said H. C. Littooy has a clear and adequate remedy in teh State Court, to-wit, the Superior Court of the State of Washington which is the proper tribunal to adjudicate any of the questions involved herein.
Prosecuting Attorney of King County, Washignton.
Samuel R. Stern, Counsel to Washington State Board of Dental Examiners.
IN THE Circuit COURT OF THE UNITED STATES FOR THE DISTRICT OF WASHINGTON
In the matter of H. C. Littooy for Writ of Habeas Corpus
S. R. Stern for The State of Washington
